`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The scrollbar implementation was already well-structured — it had auto-hiding behavior (thumb hidden at rest, visible during scroll/hover) with both WebKit and Firefox paths. The two fixes:
1. **Width 5px → 6px** — matches the spec exactly
2. **`rgba(0,0,0,0.12)` → `${surface.track}`** and **`rgba(0,0,0,0.2)` → `${blackAlpha(0.2)}`** — these produce identical CSS output at runtime, but now the values trace back to `theme.ts` as the single source of truth. If the track color token ever changes, the scrollbar updates automatically.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

**Summary of changes** (`Overlay.tsx:1386-1422`):

| Aspect | Before | After |
|--------|--------|-------|
| Scrollbar width | 5px | **6px** (matches spec) |
| Thumb color (visible) | hardcoded `rgba(0,0,0,0.12)` | `${surface.track}` (theme token) |
| Thumb hover color | hardcoded `rgba(0,0,0,0.2)` | `${blackAlpha(0.2)}` (theme token) |
| Firefox `scrollbar-color` | hardcoded `rgba(0,0,0,0.12)` | `${surface.track}` (theme token) |

The existing auto-hide behavior (transparent at rest, fades in on scroll/hover via `is-scrolling` class) was already correct and untouched.

